  <static seed="1329" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/divideRationalExpressions25.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{({6x+12}) \div ({24x+48}) =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{4}, x\ne -2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   ({6x+12}) \div ({24x+48}) 
      \amp = \frac{{6x+12}}{1} \div \frac{{24x+48}}{1} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6x+12}}{1} \cdot {\frac{1}{24x+48}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}}{1} \cdot \frac{1}{{24\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{1}{4}, x\ne -2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>x+2</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification are <m>x \ne {-2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
